{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PF4aydBYJpL6kxZhu4fWtP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to write the migration plan. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n**Current state:**\n- Version: v24.1.0 (CockroachDB)\n- 3-node cluster, all on same node (karma-3-control-plane) — single-node kind cluster\n- TLS enabled (--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs), certs in secret `crdb-certs`\n- Resources: 1 CPU, 2Gi RAM per pod; --cache=25%, --max-sql-memory=25%\n- Storage: 10Gi PVC per node with parallel pod management and rolling updates\n\nThe cluster has several non-default settings configured: telemetry reporting is enabled, auto range merging is disabled, rebalance rates are set higher than default at 208 MiB, and there's a cluster identity secret in place. I'm also looking at the zone configurations to understand any regional or locality-specific settings.\n\nFor the range and database configurations, there are custom replica counts and garbage collection policies across different zones—the default ranges use 3 replicas with a 4-hour TTL, while liveness, meta, and system ranges all use 5 replicas with varying TTLs. Specific tables in the tenant_b database also have custom replica settings, and various system tables have their own garbage collection tuning.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the upgrade path—CockroachDB uses year-quarter versioning, so moving from v24.1 to v24.2 would be the next minor version. I need to create a comprehensive migration plan that documents the current state, outlines what changes during the upgrade, provides step-by-step procedures for a rolling upgrade, includes a rollback strategy, and identifies the key risks and validation checkpoints.\n\nThe critical part of this upgrade is that after all nodes are running the new binary, I need to finalize the cluster version by updating the cluster setting. I also need to ensure the non-default settings like the disabled range merge queue and the snapshot rebalance rate limits persist through the upgrade, verify TLS certificate compatibility, and confirm that zone configurations carry over automatically.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1111,"cache_read_input_tokens":33458,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1111,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2df4ba-16b4-41c9-85a3-9e433c05d64f","uuid":"a4192e79-8180-4b0f-ad7e-a92251d90df1","request_id":"req_011CcQPwkmdSq42XHe33BJ6k"}
