{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PF4aydBYJpL6kxZhu4fWtP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UwY1CBVtseVWq7E1H71gfL","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# CockroachDB v24.1 → v24.2 Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-25  \n**Status:** DRAFT — for peer review; not yet approved for execution  \n**Target window:** Separate maintenance window (TBD)  \n**Cluster namespace:** `cockroachdb`  \n**Author:** Platform Engineering (via automated inspection)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Software Version\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Image | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` |\n| Build tag | v24.1.0 (2024-05-15) |\n| Active cluster version | `24.1` |\n| Go runtime | go1.22.2 |\n| TLS mode | TLS enabled (`--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`) |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Replicas (StatefulSet) | 3 |\n| Nodes | crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2 |\n| Pod management policy | Parallel |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition=0) |\n| Headless service | `crdb-cluster` (26257/TCP, 8080/TCP) |\n| Public service | `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP 10.96.241.54) |\n| TLS certificates | Secret `crdb-certs` (Opaque, 5 keys) |\n\n### 1.3 Resource Allocation\n\n| Resource | Request | Limit |\n|----------|---------|-------|\n| CPU | 1 core | 1 core |\n| Memory | 2 Gi | 2 Gi |\n| Disk (PVC per node) | 10 Gi | — |\n\nNode start flags: `--cache=25%` (≈512 MiB), `--max-sql-memory=25%` (≈512 MiB)\n\n### 1.4 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\nThese settings differ from CockroachDB factory defaults and must be preserved post-upgrade:\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default | Notes |\n|----------|--------------|---------|-------|\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | `true` | `false` | Telemetry reporting opted in |\n| `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled` | `false` | `true` | Automatic range merging disabled |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | `208 MiB` | `32 MiB` | Rebalance rate raised ~6.5× |\n| `cluster.secret` | `7f032057-b5df-497f-99c9-2c8e9a7e7aea` | *(empty)* | Auto-generated identity; preserved automatically |\n| `version` | `24.1` | `unsupported` | Will advance to `24.2` in finalization step |\n\n### 1.5 Zone Configurations\n\nAll explicit zone overrides in effect (verified via `crdb_internal.zones`):\n\n#### Internal range zones\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | range_min_bytes | range_max_bytes |\n|--------|-------------|--------------|-----------------|-----------------|\n| `RANGE default` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE liveness` | 5 | 600 (10 min) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE meta` | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `RANGE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n| `DATABASE system` | 5 | 14400 (4 h) | 128 MiB | 512 MiB |\n\n#### System table overrides (gc.ttlseconds only unless noted)\n| Target | gc.ttlseconds |\n|--------|--------------|\n| `system.public.lease` | 600 (10 min) |\n| `system.public.replication_constraint_stats` | 600 (10 min) |\n| `system.public.replication_stats` | 600 (10 min) |\n| `system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries` | 3600 (1 h) |\n| `system.public.statement_activity` | 3600 (1 h) |\n| `system.public.statement_statistics` | 3600 (1 h) |\n| `system.public.tenant_usage` | 7200 (2 h) |\n| `system.public.transaction_activity` | 3600 (1 h) |\n| `system.public.transaction_statistics` | 3600 (1 h) |\n\n#### Application table overrides\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds |\n|--------|-------------|--------------|\n| `defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) |\n| `defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d` | 3 | 14400 (4 h) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. What Will Change\n\n### 2.1 Image Tag (the only change executed during the window)\n\n```\ncockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0  →  cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\nThe exact patch (`x`) should be pinned to the latest v24.2 release available at\nexecution time. Check https://www.cockroachlabs.com/docs/releases/ before the window.\n\n### 2.2 Active Cluster Version Setting\n\nAfter all three nodes are running the v24.2 binary and healthy, the cluster\nversion is finalized:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2';\n```\n\nThis is a one-way operation — there is no downgrade path once finalized.\n\n### 2.3 New Default Behaviors in v24.2 (Review Before Execution)\n\nCockroachDB v24.2 ships several behavioral changes that may interact with the\nnon-default settings above:\n\n- **Range merge queue** (`kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false`): verify this\n  setting is still recognized and respected in v24.2; the setting name may have\n  been deprecated or renamed.\n- **Snapshot rebalance rate** (`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 208 MiB`):\n  confirm the setting is not superseded by a new admission-control mechanism\n  introduced in v24.2.\n- **Diagnostics reporting**: verify the reporting endpoint URL has not changed.\n- **Zone config schema**: v24.2 may introduce new zone config fields; existing\n  zones are forward-compatible but should be spot-checked post-upgrade.\n- **New system tables**: v24.2 may add system tables with their own default zone\n  configs; these will not inherit the custom overrides above and should be\n  reviewed.\n\n### 2.4 What Does NOT Change\n\n- Zone configurations — preserved in the KV store, not affected by binary upgrade.\n- Cluster settings — preserved in the KV store; `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled`,\n  `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`, and `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` all\n  survive the rolling restart.\n- PVC data — not touched; data lives on `datadir-crdb-cluster-{0,1,2}`.\n- TLS certificates — secret `crdb-certs` is unchanged; cert rotation is a\n  separate operation.\n- Resource limits/requests — unchanged (1 CPU / 2 Gi per pod).\n- Service topology — headless + public services unchanged.\n- `--cache` / `--max-sql-memory` flags — unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade 